text = "[center][b][color=#ffd966]Forge Gameplay System – Demo Hub[/color][/b][/center]

[color=#cccccc]
This hub showcases two simple demos focused on demonstrating how Forge handles [b]Gameplay Effects[/b], [b]Abilities[/b], and [b]effect interactions[/b].[/color]

[hr]

[b][color=#6fa8dc]Demo A – Real-Time 3D[/color][/b]  
[color=#dddddd]
A real-time 3D scene featuring a player and two basic enemies (approach and attack behavior only).[/color]

• [color=#ff6d6d]Fire Area[/color]: 10 elemental damage over time, spreads when the source entity is on fire and causes damage.
• [color=#6d9eeb]Water Area[/color]: removes and prevents Fire.
• [color=#f1c232]Instant Damage Area[/color]: 100 instant physical damage.
• [color=#93c47d]Regen Area[/color]: instant heal (50) + up to 3 heal over time stacks (10/s).

[color=#dddddd]Also includes:[/color]

• 3D Healing ShapeCast (applies while inside, removed on exit).
• 3D Water RayCast.

[color=#dddddd]Movement: [b]WASD / Arrow Keys[/b].
Player has natural regeneration: [b]+1 Health/s[/b] and [b]+1 Mana/s[/b].[/color]

[color=#ffffff][b]Abilities[/b][/color]

• [b]Projectile[/b] (Mouse 1): projectile, distance-scaled damage, can be set on Fire.
• [b]Dash[/b] (Space): dash toward mouse direction, temporary physical immunity.
• [b]Shield[/b] (3): toggle, reduces damage by 80%, consumes 20 mana per hit.
• [b]Reflect[/b] (Passive): on physical damage taken, triggers an AoE damage reflection.

[hr]

[b][color=#8e7cc`3]Demo B – Turn-Based 2D[/color][/b]
[color=#dddddd]A 2D scene focused on turn-based effects.
Time only advances when you move.[/color]

• 2D Areas, ShapeCasts, and RayCasts.
• Same effects and durations as the 3D demo.
• Each turn = 1 second.
• Damage and healing over time apply only when moving.

[color=#bbbbbb]Ideal for visualizing effects adapted to turn-based systems.[/color]"

